						               													<description>&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#170;&amp;#233;&amp;#153;&amp;#189;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#233;&amp;#155;&amp;#168;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#232;&amp;#153;&amp;#185;  (&amp;quot;Sun, Rain and Rainbow&amp;quot;) is a card game. The cards consist of 36 cards in 7 color suits. Each suit has either a Sun or Rain(s). The color of suit can be recognized by the card back. The box comes with 4 games (with their rulebooks): &amp;quot;Sun Rummy&amp;rdquo;, &amp;quot;Rain Go Out&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Rainbow Trick&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Weather Line&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Lamii of the Sun&amp;quot;&amp;#10;Put the card in your place and make a role. By recombining the cards in the field and making good use of the special effects of the roles, you can create a role with a higher score and aim for a higher score by rising faster.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Rain go out&amp;quot;&amp;#10;I will put out cards of the same color or continuous colors face down. I don't even know if it's &amp;quot;rainy&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;sunny&amp;quot;. By reading and intuition, I will compete to get out of my hand as soon as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Rainbow Trick&amp;quot;&amp;#10;An anomalous trick-taking game where you control the points you earn. The winner will take the card by comparing the strength of the cards issued by everyone. Repeat this process, calculate the points you can get with the cards you get, and compete for points according to the points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Weather line&amp;quot;&amp;#10;Cards are put out alternately to make a four-row line. Compare the number of &amp;quot;own teams&amp;quot; for each row, and the one with the most will conquer that row. Compete for victory or defeat by the total number of conquered rows.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
